  "prompt": "What does President Duterte think of Donald Trump?",
  "response": "President Rodrigo Duterte of the Philippines had a complex relationship with former President Donald Trump during Trump's time in office. Duterte initially praised Trump, appreciating his straightforward approach and perceived strong leadership style. He expressed admiration for Trump\u2019s policies and often noted that he saw a similarity in their leadership styles.\n\nHowever, Duterte's fondness for Trump was also mixed with a pragmatic approach to international relations. He occasionally criticized the U.S. and its policies, especially when he felt they interfered with Philippine sovereignty or domestic policies. Duterte's admiration for Trump contrasted with his more confrontational stance towards former President Barack Obama, whom he publicly criticized.\n\nOverall, while Duterte expressed positive views about Trump, the relationship was multifaceted, reflecting both respect and geopolitical pragmatism.",
